00:14:11,333 --> 00:14:14,750
But there's no way you can
talk to your mother about it.

251
00:14:14,833 --> 00:14:17,000
My real father left
behind so much debt

252
00:14:17,083 --> 00:14:20,875
that it'd be impossible for my
mom to pay it off on her own.

253
00:14:20,958 --> 00:14:23,875
So we have to
depend on that man.

254
00:14:23,958 --> 00:14:25,750
But at my regular
checkup last week,

255
00:14:25,833 --> 00:14:29,541
they said my Psycho-Pass
had gotten all cloudy.

256
00:14:29,625 --> 00:14:32,500
As it is I might...

257
00:14:36,708 --> 00:14:37,625
Yoshika.

258
00:14:37,708 --> 00:14:38,833
It feels like you're not allowed

259
00:14:38,916 --> 00:14:41,125
to choose the life you
wish you could live.

260
00:14:41,208 --> 00:14:43,833
I understand how hard that is.

261
00:14:43,916 --> 00:14:47,708
In this day and age the
System determines our aptitudes

262
00:14:47,791 --> 00:14:51,875
and we have no choice but to
live by that and be satisfied

263
00:14:51,958 --> 00:14:54,916
with just whatever happiness
is forced upon us,

264
00:14:55,000 --> 00:14:56,375
unable and unpermitted

265
00:14:56,458 --> 00:14:59,541
to make any of our
real dreams a reality.

266
00:15:01,541 --> 00:15:03,791
The person that you long to be.

267
00:15:03,875 --> 00:15:05,875
Your true worth in this world.

268
00:15:05,958 --> 00:15:08,875
Don't you want to at least
try to discover that?

269
00:15:11,125 --> 00:15:13,291
I can show you, Yoshika.

270
00:15:13,375 --> 00:15:17,625
The beauty that's hiding inside
you, just below the surface.

271
00:15:27,375 --> 00:15:31,333
Would you like to hear some
more about Shakespeare's work?

272
00:15:31,416 --> 00:15:32,583
Please.

273
00:15:32,666 --> 00:15:35,041
Let's start with
Titus Andronicus.

274
00:15:35,125 --> 00:15:38,541
My favorite character in that
one is Titus' daughter, Lavinia.

275
00:15:38,625 --> 00:15:41,041
She was punished for
the sins of her father.

276
00:15:41,125 --> 00:15:44,416
His enemies raped her, and then,
so she couldn't tell anyone.

277
00:15:44,500 --> 00:15:49,208
they cut out her tongue
and chopped off her arms.

278
00:15:49,291 --> 00:15:50,916
"and he that wounded her Hath

279
00:15:51,000 --> 00:15:54,000
hurt me more than
had he killed me dead".

280
00:15:54,083 --> 00:15:57,625
Poor Lavinia. In the end,

281
00:15:57,708 --> 00:16:00,708
put to death at the
hand of her own father.

282
00:16:08,625 --> 00:16:09,875
There are millions of things.

283
00:16:09,958 --> 00:16:13,708
that we humans are capable
of but animals are not.

284
00:16:13,791 --> 00:16:16,750
One of those things
is safety control.

285
00:16:16,833 --> 00:16:18,500
No matter what we create,

286
00:16:18,583 --> 00:16:21,666
humans always put a
safety mechanism on it.

287
00:16:21,750 --> 00:16:24,166
Enforcers are equipped
with a safety mechanism

288
00:16:24,250 --> 00:16:26,041
in the form of Inspectors.

289
00:16:26,125 --> 00:16:29,166
And the Drones you
controlled were furnished

290
00:16:29,250 --> 00:16:32,833
with their own set of
rigorous security measures.

291
00:16:32,916 --> 00:16:36,500
Those Drones were supposed
to be absolutely safe,

292
00:16:36,583 --> 00:16:39,625
and yet, this memory
card made them kill people.

293
00:16:42,000 --> 00:16:45,291
Where did you obtain it?

294
00:16:49,458 --> 00:16:51,041
The safety override
program that Kanehara put

295
00:16:51,125 --> 00:16:54,083
to use in the
Hachioji Drone incident

296
00:16:54,166 --> 00:16:56,416
and then Mido's
Holograph cracking.

297
00:16:56,500 --> 00:16:59,000
Well, in both of those
instances I was only able

298
00:16:59,083 --> 00:17:01,708
to recover a small
fragment of the source code.

299
00:17:01,791 --> 00:17:03,625
but there are
clear similarities.

300
00:17:03,708 --> 00:17:06,500
I think the same programmer
wrote code for both.

301
00:17:06,583 --> 00:17:09,875
Hell, I'm so sure of that, I'd
bet the bra I'm wearing on it.

302
00:17:09,958 --> 00:17:11,416
Keep it please.

303
00:17:11,500 --> 00:17:14,458
Mido may have been overly
obsessed with social networks.

304
00:17:14,541 --> 00:17:16,625
but he didn't possess
the skills necessary

305
00:17:16,708 --> 00:17:19,541
to tamper with public
Holo to that degree.

306
00:17:19,625 --> 00:17:22,125
There's no mistaking the
fact that Kanehara and Mido

307
00:17:22,208 --> 00:17:25,000
were both being backed by a
professional cyber-criminal.

308
00:17:25,083 --> 00:17:26,333
Yeah, but this testimony

309
00:17:26,416 --> 00:17:29,625
from Kanehara isn't gonna
help us any, is it, now?

310
00:17:29,708 --> 00:17:30,833
I swear!

311
00:17:30,916 --> 00:17:32,375
It was just sent to me
in the mail one day,

312
00:17:32,458 --> 00:17:33,708
clear out of the blue!

313
00:17:33,791 --> 00:17:36,125
The letter wasn't signed;
there was no name on it.

314
00:17:36,208 --> 00:17:38,250
All it said was he had a
grudge against the factory

315
00:17:38,333 --> 00:17:40,625
so he wanted us
to destroy it together!

316
00:17:40,708 --> 00:17:42,041
Pretty vicious.

317
00:17:42,125 --> 00:17:44,041
Seems this person
will kill for kicks.

318
00:17:44,125 --> 00:17:45,875
How could whoever sent
that letter have predicted

319
00:17:45,958 --> 00:17:49,500
that Kanehara would be open
to killing in the first place?

320
00:17:49,583 --> 00:17:50,375
Why not?

321
00:17:50,458 --> 00:17:51,708
Pops had Kanehara figured out

322
00:17:51,791 --> 00:17:54,583
just by looking at the
staff's periodic checkups.

323
00:17:54,666 --> 00:17:57,000
Surely someone else could've
done the same thing.

324
00:17:57,083 --> 00:18:00,375
It's not like those evaluation
files were kept confidential.

325
00:18:00,458 --> 00:18:04,083
So what's this guy's
motive for helping Mido?

326
00:18:04,166 --> 00:18:06,916
It was Kanehara and
Mido who had the motives.

327
00:18:07,000 --> 00:18:10,708
And that would be more than
enough of a reason for him.

328
00:18:11,583 --> 00:18:12,458
Kogami?

329
00:18:12,541 --> 00:18:14,416
Intent and means.

330
00:18:14,500 --> 00:18:16,458
Engineering a crime
by bringing together

331
00:18:16,541 --> 00:18:19,791
those two otherwise
disparate elements.

332
00:18:19,875 --> 00:18:23,166
That's how he plays his game.

333
00:18:32,833 --> 00:18:34,166
Hey!

334
00:18:42,083 --> 00:18:43,500
Kogami you can't keep...

335
00:18:43,583 --> 00:18:45,708
Gino, it's the
same as that case.

336
00:18:45,791 --> 00:18:47,666
Someone out there is
providing the means to people

337
00:18:47,750 --> 00:18:50,500
who have the desire to kill,
but don't know how.

338
00:18:50,583 --> 00:18:53,791
Turning these wannabes
into actual murderers.

339
00:18:56,000 --> 00:18:57,458
Stop and think this through.

340
00:18:57,541 --> 00:18:59,250
Back then they used a resin.

341
00:18:59,333 --> 00:19:01,958
But this time, it was a
tool for cracking programs.

342
00:19:02,041 --> 00:19:03,958
There's no connection.

343
00:19:04,041 --> 00:19:07,041
The engineer and the middleman
are two different people!

344
00:19:07,125 --> 00:19:09,375
There's somebody who
brings them together.

345
00:19:09,458 --> 00:19:10,791
Those who wish to kill and those

346
00:19:10,875 --> 00:19:13,541
who can create the weapons
they need to pull it off.

347
00:19:13,625 --> 00:19:15,375
That's the real mastermind.

348
00:19:15,458 --> 00:19:16,916
Enough of this!

349
00:19:17,000 --> 00:19:19,416
You've been chasing
a damn ghost!

350
00:19:19,500 --> 00:19:21,458
One that may never have existed!

351
00:19:22,125 --> 00:19:25,125
Sasayama was on the
verge of a breakthrough.

352
00:19:25,208 --> 00:19:27,083
I'll settle this score for him.

353
00:19:27,166 --> 00:19:30,416
That's what I've been working
towards for three years.

354
00:19:36,958 --> 00:19:39,125
It's Takahashi from
Public Cleaning Bureau.

355
00:19:39,208 --> 00:19:41,250
Yeah, I'm over at the
Central Fountain Tower.

356
00:19:41,333 --> 00:19:44,333
Noise has been in the
Hologram for a while.

357
00:19:44,416 --> 00:19:45,583
Yeah, that's right.

358
00:19:45,666 --> 00:19:47,166
You mind turning off
the fountain Holo

359
00:19:47,250 --> 00:19:48,708
so we can check it out?

360
00:19:53,666 --> 00:19:55,291
What the hell?

361
00:19:56,458 --> 00:19:59,375
Whoa that's creepy!
Is it a doll?

362
00:20:02,125 --> 00:20:04,916
Looks like some kinda art
project or something.

363
00:20:05,000 --> 00:20:05,958
Huh, maybe.

364
00:20:06,041 --> 00:20:08,250
Whatever it is,
it's in poor taste.

365
00:20:08,333 --> 00:20:10,333
It's gross. Who did this?

366
00:20:16,375 --> 00:20:21,333
Y'know, when you get up close,
it looks pretty damn real.

367
00:20:22,708 --> 00:20:24,708
Such detail.

368
00:20:25,875 --> 00:20:27,708
Still. I don't
think I'd want that

369
00:20:27,791 --> 00:20:30,291
on display anywhere in my house.

370
00:20:39,791 --> 00:20:43,166
I'm curious. Do you think
Lavinia was happy at last?

371
00:20:43,250 --> 00:20:46,500
Finally liberated from her
violated body?

372
00:20:46,583 --> 00:20:48,333
It's like Saturninus
says in Act Five,

373
00:20:48,416 --> 00:20:49,791
just before Titus kills her.

374
00:20:49,875 --> 00:20:52,000
"Because the girl should
not survive her shame,

375
00:20:52,083 --> 00:20:54,708
And by her presence
still renew his sorrows.".

376
00:20:54,791 --> 00:20:57,125
Is that right. Mister Makishima?

377
00:20:57,208 --> 00:21:00,083
Even beautiful flowers
eventually wither and fall.

378
00:21:00,166 --> 00:21:01,750
It's a fate that
meets all living things,

379
00:21:01,833 --> 00:21:03,333
one way or another.

380
00:21:03,416 --> 00:21:06,875
Knowing that sad fact, it's only
natural to want to stop time,

381
00:21:06,958 --> 00:21:10,208
preserving the blossom
while still in full bloom.

382
00:21:10,291 --> 00:21:13,041
But if you did truly
love the girl as though

383
00:21:13,125 --> 00:21:14,458
she were your own daughter,

384
00:21:14,541 --> 00:21:17,458
do you believe that you,
too, will be moved to say.

385
00:21:17,541 --> 00:21:19,125
"Kill'd her for whom my tears

386
00:21:19,208 --> 00:21:22,458
have made me blind."
as Titus was?

387
00:21:22,541 --> 00:21:24,750
Oh, that might be
a problem for me

388
00:21:24,833 --> 00:21:28,125
because I have many
more works of art

389
00:21:28,208 --> 00:21:30,833
that I wish to complete
in the days that lie ahead.

390
00:21:30,916 --> 00:21:32,333
I'm just getting started.

